documentation.text: @title Auction interface

@dev emitted when admin create an auction
 @param auctionId  is id of auction
@dev set {_address} to TreeFactory contract address
@dev set {_address} to Allocation contract address
@dev set {_address} to WethFund contract address
@dev set {_address} to RegularSale contract address
@dev set {_address} to WethToken contract address

@dev user bid for {_auctionId} in a time beetwen start time and end time
 NOTE its require to send at least {higestBid + bidInterval } {_amount}.
 NOTE if new bid done old bidder refund automatically.
 NOTE if user bid 10 minutes left to auction end, auction's end time increase 10 minute
 NOTE emit a {HighestBidIncreased} event
 NOTE emit an {AuctionEndTimeIncreased} if user bids less than 10 minutes left to auction end
 @param _auctionId auctionId that user bid for it.

@dev end auction and mint tree to winner if auction has bidder
 and tree funded based on allocation data for that tree
 NOTE if winner has referrer, claimable trees of that referrer increase by 1
 NOTE if auction does not have bidder, saleType of tree in auction reset
 and admin can put that tree in another auction
 NOTE emit an {AuctionSettled} event if auction has bidder
 NOTE emit an {AuctionEnded} event if auction does not have bidder
 @param _auctionId id of auction to end.
@return true if Auction contract has been initialized
@title Auction interface

@dev emitted when admin create an auction
 @param auctionId  is id of auction
@dev set {_address} to TreeFactory contract address
@dev set {_address} to Allocation contract address
@dev set {_address} to WethFund contract address
@dev set {_address} to RegularSale contract address
@dev set {_address} to WethToken contract address

@dev user bid for {_auctionId} in a time beetwen start time and end time
 NOTE its require to send at least {higestBid + bidInterval } {_amount}.
 NOTE if new bid done old bidder refund automatically.
 NOTE if user bid 10 minutes left to auction end, auction's end time increase 10 minute
 NOTE emit a {HighestBidIncreased} event
 NOTE emit an {AuctionEndTimeIncreased} if user bids less than 10 minutes left to auction end
 @param _auctionId auctionId that user bid for it.

@dev end auction and mint tree to winner if auction has bidder
 and tree funded based on allocation data for that tree
 NOTE if winner has referrer, claimable trees of that referrer increase by 1
 NOTE if auction does not have bidder, saleType of tree in auction reset
 and admin can put that tree in another auction
 NOTE emit an {AuctionSettled} event if auction has bidder
 NOTE emit an {AuctionEnded} event if auction does not have bidder
 @param _auctionId id of auction to end.
@return true if Auction contract has been initialized

AuctionCreated(uint256).details: emitted when admin create an auction

AuctionEndTimeIncreased(uint256,uint256).details: emmited when user bids less than 10 minutes left to the end of auction

params.auctionId: id of auction to increase end time
params.newAuctionEndTime: new value of auction end time

AuctionEnded(uint256,uint256).details: emitted when auction end and there is no bidder.

AuctionSettled(uint256,uint256,address,u.details: emitted when auction ended and there is winner

HighestBidIncreased(uint256,uint256,addr.details: emitted when new bid done for auction

params.auctionId: id of auction that bid done for

auctions(uint256).details: return data of an auction with {_auctionId}

params._auctionId: id of auction to get data

bid(uint256,uint256,address).details: user bid for {_auctionId} in a time beetwen start time and end time NOTE its require to send at least {higestBid + bidInterval } {_amount}. NOTE if new bid done old bidder refund automatically. NOTE if user bid 10 minutes left to auction end, auction's end time increase 10 minute NOTE emit a {HighestBidIncreased} event NOTE emit an {AuctionEndTimeIncreased} if user bids less than 10 minutes left to auction end

params._auctionId: auctionId that user bid for it.

createAuction(uint256,uint64,uint64,uint.details: admin put a tree with saleType of '0' in auction. NOTE set saleType to '1' to that tree NOTE its necessary that a allocation data has been assigned to {_treeId} NOTE emit an {AuctionCreated} event

params._bidInterval: bid interval for auction.if it set to 10 for example and the last bid is 100.new bidder can bid at least for 110

endAuction(uint256,uint256).details: end auction and mint tree to winner if auction has bidder and tree funded based on allocation data for that tree NOTE if winner has referrer, claimable trees of that referrer increase by 1 NOTE if auction does not have bidder, saleType of tree in auction reset and admin can put that tree in another auction NOTE emit an {AuctionSettled} event if auction has bidder NOTE emit an {AuctionEnded} event if auction does not have bidder

returns._0: true if Auction contract has been initialized

referrals(address,uint256).details: return referrer address of {_bidder} in auction with id {_auctionId}
